{
  "info": {
    "name": "Transactions Service",
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "description": "Manages cardholder accounts and the transactions posted against them.\n\nPurchases and withdrawals are stored as negative amounts; credit vouchers are positive. The caller always sends a **positive** amount — the server applies the sign based on the operation type.\n\n## Quick start\n1. Start the service: `./run` (or `go run ./cmd/api`)\n2. Run **Create Account** — the test script stores the returned `account_id` in the `accountId` collection variable automatically.\n3. Run any **Create Transaction** request.\n\n## Operation types\n| ID | Description | Sign |\n|----|-------------|------|\n| 1  | Normal Purchase | − |\n| 2  | Purchase with installments | − |\n| 3  | Withdrawal | − |\n| 4  | Credit Voucher | + |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of the running service"
    },
    {
      "key": "accountId",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Set automatically by the Create Account test script"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
